You flip a fair coin 576 times. Without using a calculator, calculate the probability of flipping at least 312 heads.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This question requires some memorization. At first glance we can infer that it’s a binomial distribution problem given that we have to guess the number of heads out of a number of trials. Therefore similar to a binomial distribution with 
�
