We now can figure out that 312 is 2 standard deviations above the mean given that 24 + 288 = 312.

So due to the binomial approximation to the normal distribution, we know that at 
±
± 2 standard deviations that 5% of the distribution is on the tails, which means 2.5% chance of 312 or more heads.
